summary: This document is a search and seizure warrant issued by the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York. It authorizes law enforcement to search specific binders and CDs believed to contain evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy. The warrant outlines the items to be seized and the legal basis for the search.

persons.name: Kelly Maguire
persons.context: Kelly Maguire is mentioned as the Special Agent who seized various binders and CDs from suitcases during the investigation.

persons.name: Hon. L. Cott
persons.context: Hon. L. Cott is the judge who signed the search warrant, authorizing the search and seizure.

connections.description: Kelly Maguire, as a Special Agent, is involved in the execution of the search warrant authorized by Judge Hon. L. Cott.

events.title: Seizure of Evidence
events.description: Special Agent Kelly Maguire seized two blue binders and various CDs from suitcases as part of the investigation into sex trafficking.

events.title: Issuance of Search Warrant
events.description: A search warrant was issued by the court to authorize the search and seizure of specific items believed to contain evidence of sex trafficking.

keyFacts: The search warrant was issued to search for evidence related to violations of sex trafficking laws.
Special Agent Kelly Maguire seized binders and CDs from suitcases on July 11, 2019.
The warrant allows law enforcement to review electronic stored information for evidence of sex trafficking of minors.
Immediate notification of the warrant execution was authorized to be delayed due to potential adverse results.
The warrant specifies the types of evidence sought, including documents and photographs related to victims.
